\intbl \ql \b Summary of Evaluator Report\b0 \line The evaluator indicated that all minimum standards pertaining to the criteria assessed have been met with the exception of Criterion 4. As is the case with the Advanced Certificate it would appear that a number of aspects regarding the distance education mode of delivery need clarification.\line The evaluator stated that the programme supports studies in the field of Psychology and more specifically the field of the lay counsellor. There is an urgent need for lay counsellors in the South African context and the programme design meets the minimum criteria. A comprehensive module outline and prescribed readings are provided. The evaluator\'2C however\'2C indicated that there are sometimes assessment opportunities which do not seem to be in line with distance education \'28for example open book tests and role plays\'29 and it is not clear how distance students will participate in the Admissions Protocol and the comprehensive assessment writing workshop. \line The Directorate does not concur with the recommendation that the programme should be accredited\'2C but recommends that the decision should be deferred pending clarification on the distance education concerns raised.  \line \cell \pard 

